#. EDID: SFFL_SE_EC01_GloriaHomework_ScienceEssay
#. REC: TMLM:BTXT
msgctxt "000ED8"
msgid "Grav Jumping: How We Bend Space to Travel the Stars\nBy Gloria Swansen, age 15\n\nBy allowing ships to cross vast distances faster than the speed of light, Grav jumping is the most important technology with regards to space travel. It can bring distant points close to each other by temporarily bending spacetime, so ships can then move between them in an instant.\n\nThe gravity drive creates a controlled singularity bubble that lets the ship bypass normal spacetime to \"jump\" at its destination. The energy required depends on the distance traveled and the mass of the ship. Grav wells stabilize the process, ensuring ships exit the jump safely.\n\nGrav jumping is very useful, but it has its risks. Navigation errors can cause a ship to exit a jump off-course or in dangerous areas. Nearby planets and stars can also interfere with the jump. That's why grav jump systems are strictly regulated, and pilots follow strict protocols when jumping.\n\nThanks to grav jumping, interstellar travel is possible, allowing people to explore distant star systems. While the technology continues to evolve, it has already shaped how we move through the universe."
msgstr ""

