#. List: 0
#. EDID: SFFL_MS01_Ivica_TMLM
#. REC: TMLM:UNAM
msgctxt "000F00"
msgid "Caruso hinted the other day that until we get more workers, we should consider repairing some of the machines to take on the labor.\n\nI did my best not to spit in his face. Machines make MORE work, not less, because they do a mediocre job. Everyone knows this.\n\n"
msgstr ""

#. List: 0
#. EDID: SFFL_MS01_Ivica_TMLM
#. REC: TMLM:ITXT
msgctxt "000F01"
msgid "More Workers, Not Machines"
msgstr ""

#. List: 0
#. EDID: SFFL_MS01_Ivica_TMLM
#. REC: TMLM:UNAM
msgctxt "000F02"
msgid "Zena seems to be grooming Caruso to be her successor, but I don't know where Caruso stands on the topic of rest stop vs. refinery.\n\nOn the one hand, he seems like a practical man. Straightforward, hard-working, with none of the gluposti that the younger folks pine for.\n\nBut it seems he's bought into this idea of togetherness and community which infects the mind like a disease. Does he think I will ever respect or value someone like Sunni if we sat at the same dinner table? No, I will respect her when she puts in the work.\n\nTalk is cheap. Effort is free."
msgstr ""

#. List: 0
#. EDID: SFFL_MS01_Ivica_TMLM
#. REC: TMLM:ITXT
msgctxt "000F03"
msgid "Caruso"
msgstr ""

#. List: 0
#. EDID: SFFL_MS01_Ivica_TMLM
#. REC: TMLM:UNAM
msgctxt "000F04"
msgid "The Helium-3 yields have been strong this year, and I think we can strike a long term deal with HopeTech to transport the goods.\n\nZena wants this outpost to be a \"rest stop,\" but that's utopian nonsense, an ideal carried over from Alphonse's time. It's far better as a mining outpost. We take the scrap, recycle it into a refinery, and we profit. \n\nCredits are what sustain us, not people or community or all this other crap."
msgstr ""

#. List: 0
#. EDID: SFFL_MS01_Ivica_TMLM
#. REC: TMLM:ITXT
msgctxt "000F05"
msgid "Future of New Babylon"
msgstr ""

