#. List: 0
#. EDID: SFFL_AnchorpointSH_Notes
#. REC: TMLM:UNAM
msgctxt "000F31"
msgid "My plan worked!\n\nI now have the companionship I so desired from my Security compatriots! Finally, I am able to dine with others rather than in my chambers.\n\nThey've even started assisting me in my game! One of them revealed that the chambers of Rishi Saint are commonly left unguarded and unlocked, suggesting that this would be the perfect place for my final clue.\n\nGenius! How grateful I am to have companions such as these."
msgstr ""

#. List: 0
#. EDID: SFFL_AnchorpointSH_Notes
#. REC: TMLM:ITXT
msgctxt "000F32"
msgid "[5/5] A New Challenge"
msgstr ""

#. List: 0
#. EDID: SFFL_AnchorpointSH_Notes
#. REC: TMLM:UNAM
msgctxt "000F33"
msgid "I decided that the time for moping has passed. My orders are to infiltrate and gather information for the Armada, not to give up and go home.\n\nI will do whatever I can to make lemonade of the situation. Friends and companionship are the antidote to my melancholy. Misery loves company, but so do I. \n\nI must contort myself to become more amicable. Dampen my passions and perform the role of boredom and aloofness. That will win them over to my side, surely."
msgstr ""

#. List: 0
#. EDID: SFFL_AnchorpointSH_Notes
#. REC: TMLM:ITXT
msgctxt "000F34"
msgid "[4/5] Turning the Page"
msgstr ""

#. List: 0
#. EDID: SFFL_AnchorpointSH_Notes
#. REC: TMLM:UNAM
msgctxt "000F35"
msgid "Last night I heard words that were not meant for my ears.\n\nI was on patrol last night when I happened upon a cracked door near the barracks. I must confess that I'm not immune to the siren call of eavesdropping, so I crept over and trained my ear to the conversation.\n\nThe other guards were laughing about me. I heard them mock my voice and speech, the attempt being more humorous to them than the accuracy.\n\nI thought we were getting along. I thought them my compatriots, my brothers and sisters in arms. I replayed my conversations with them, now seeing the mocking sneer below the performed amicability. They weren't interested in me or my games, I was an amusement to them.\n\nI retreated and continued my patrol, attempting to focus on my riddles. No one wants a tearful guard."
msgstr ""

#. List: 0
#. EDID: SFFL_AnchorpointSH_Notes
#. REC: TMLM:ITXT
msgctxt "000F36"
msgid "[3/5] Alone"
msgstr ""

#. List: 0
#. EDID: SFFL_AnchorpointSH_Notes
#. REC: TMLM:UNAM
msgctxt "000F37"
msgid "The life of a Security guard is strange.\n\nOn one hand, you're not a civilian anymore. Cleaved from society, you're now the manifestation of the law. This begets tension when interacting with civilians, they can smell your otherness. \n\nFor one such as myself, the dynamics of socializing hasn't changed. I was already at arm's length with most, my role now gives justification for it. I now also get free reign of the station, meaning I can now play my game more freely without suspicion.\n\nThe camaraderie of other Security members is a welcomed treat. Rarely have I felt the warm glow of friendship, and now I bask in it with my other members. They even seem interested in my game, asking me about my riddles and clues.\n\nI am enjoying my stay at Anchorpoint."
msgstr ""

#. List: 0
#. EDID: SFFL_AnchorpointSH_Notes
#. REC: TMLM:ITXT
msgctxt "000F38"
msgid "[2/5] New Job"
msgstr ""

#. List: 0
#. EDID: SFFL_AnchorpointSH_Notes
#. REC: TMLM:UNAM
msgctxt "000F39"
msgid "I arrived at Anchorpoint with renewed vigor. I had hoped that the rough and tumble ne'er-do-wells would accept me, a person without nation or creed, with open arms. \n\nInstead, I find the same confused looks and exhausted eyes. Those eyes, those looks, my fateful companions. My only comfort is that my station as a guard forces a stilted warmth onto otherwise empty interactions.\n\nAt least here I can play my games. My riddles. They keep my mind sharp and my environment alive."
msgstr ""

#. List: 0
#. EDID: SFFL_AnchorpointSH_Notes
#. REC: TMLM:ITXT
msgctxt "000F3A"
msgid "[1/5] Hello!"
msgstr ""

#. List: 0
#. EDID: SFFL_AnchorpointSH_Notes
#. REC: TMLM:UNAM
msgctxt "000F3B"
msgid "My last hurrah has become my undoing.\nThe Saint caught me in the act; and with the borrowed pride of a magician, I refused to elaborate on my intentions. He wouldn't understand, a mind honed for business is incapable of appreciating my game.\n\nFor the final piece, I'm imparting a token to the winner. My most prized possession, I shed a tear as I lock the safe and enact the 5 stage encryption. I also have programmed my logs to unlock in tandem, so that the one who solves my riddles can also learn my story.\n\nMy only hope is that whoever solves them feels the same sense of pride and satisfaction playing the game as I did building it.\n\nAs for me, I must away. I can't carry out my orders in prison, and so to the Free Lanes I go. \nGoodbye, Anchorpoint! Hello, adventure!"
msgstr ""

#. List: 0
#. EDID: SFFL_AnchorpointSH_Notes
#. REC: TMLM:ITXT
msgctxt "000F3C"
msgid "[0/5] Goodbye"
msgstr ""

