#. List: 0
#. EDID: SFFL_SE_EC01_GloriaHomework_HistoryUC
#. REC: TMLM:BTXT
msgctxt "000F49"
msgid "The United Colonies: A Pillar of Stability in the Settled Systems\nBy Gloria Swansen, age 15\n\nThe United Colonies (UC) is the most influential power in the Settled Systems. Since its founding in 2161, it has established a strong government, created advanced infrastructure, and maintained order across a vast territory. While other factions developed their own ways of life, the UC has remained focused on progress, stability, and security.\n\nNew Atlantis, the capital of the United Colonies, is a major center for politics, trade, and culture. With a structured government and a powerful military, the UC guards us against potential chaos as groups like the Freestar Collective push for more autonomy, and pirate groups keep attacking trade routes.\n\nDifferences with the Freestar Collective led to the Colony War in 2188, a brutal conflict that lasted almost 40 years. Tensions remain high to this day, with the Collective still rejecting offers by the UC to join our union.\n\nWhile some criticize the UC's authority, its structure and stability have made it the most powerful government in human space, ensuring that major cities, industries, and trade routes remain safe. It stands as a force dedicated to progress, so humanity can continue to build a lasting future together."
msgstr ""

#. List: 0
#. EDID: SFFL_SE_EC01_GloriaHomework_HistoryUC
#. REC: TMLM:FULL
msgctxt "000F4A"
msgid "UC History Essay"
msgstr ""

