#. EDID: SFFL_Anchorpoint_RishiSaintTerminal_MessagesSub
#. REC: TMLM:UNAM
msgctxt "000F65"
msgid "From: C. Huang\nSubject: Marin Dismissal\n\nJust got your message, Marin shouldn't be a problem anymore.\n\nPeople on Security seemed pretty relieved to hear we're firing him. Apparently he was \"a weirdo\" that didn't have any friends, so we're not missing out on much. We'll look into how he got access to your room.\n\nAlso, we were clearing out his crap and saw that he modified some of his equipment. I asked Maddie to check it out so hopefully we can reset it before we hire someone else."
msgstr ""

#. List: 0
#. EDID: SFFL_Anchorpoint_RishiSaintTerminal_MessagesSub
#. REC: TMLM:ITXT
msgctxt "000F66"
msgid "Marin Dismissal"
msgstr ""

#. List: 0
#. EDID: SFFL_Anchorpoint_RishiSaintTerminal_MessagesSub
#. REC: TMLM:UNAM
msgctxt "000F67"
msgid "From: V. Hahn\nSubject: Meeting request\n\nI'd like to meet with you when it's convenient. I want to talk about a plan for concluding my employment here, specifically how much time I have left to pay off my debt in full. I feel I've been a loyal and productive worker for you, and more than held up my end of our agreement.\n\nI find myself missing my son more with each day, and I'm very eager to discuss in detail the timeline for when I can go back home and be with him.\n\nThank you."
msgstr ""

#. List: 0
#. EDID: SFFL_Anchorpoint_RishiSaintTerminal_MessagesSub
#. REC: TMLM:ITXT
msgctxt "000F68"
msgid "Meeting request"
msgstr ""

#. List: 0
#. EDID: SFFL_Anchorpoint_RishiSaintTerminal_MessagesSub
#. REC: TMLM:UNAM
msgctxt "000F69"
msgid "From: M. Wing\nSubject: Repairs done\n\nI got that latch on your secret vault fixed up. Give the CredStik a twist and it should work like new."
msgstr ""

#. List: 0
#. EDID: SFFL_Anchorpoint_RishiSaintTerminal_MessagesSub
#. REC: TMLM:ITXT
msgctxt "000F6A"
msgid "Repairs done"
msgstr ""

#. List: 0
#. EDID: SFFL_Anchorpoint_RishiSaintTerminal_MessagesSub
#. REC: TMLM:UNAM
msgctxt "000F6B"
msgid "From: M. Wing\nSubject: I need money ASAP\n\nI know you've been avoiding me, but this station ain't big enough for you to hide forever, so you might as well just talk to me and we can get this over with. Unless of course you don't think the life support systems are all that important.\n"
msgstr ""

#. List: 0
#. EDID: SFFL_Anchorpoint_RishiSaintTerminal_MessagesSub
#. REC: TMLM:ITXT
msgctxt "000F6C"
msgid "I need money ASAP"
msgstr ""

#. List: 0
#. EDID: SFFL_Anchorpoint_RishiSaintTerminal_MessagesSub
#. REC: TMLM:UNAM
msgctxt "000F6D"
msgid "From: C. Huang\nSubject: Late payment?\n\nJust had a conversation with a very charming young lady who came to see you. Since you asked not to be disturbed, I offered to take a message. Turns out she was sent by your friend Colston in the Crimson Fleet.\n\nMister Colston seems to think you're late on your monthly dues, and sent the girl to deliver a little reminder. Threats were insinuated. I won't bore you with the particulars.\n\n"
msgstr ""

#. List: 0
#. EDID: SFFL_Anchorpoint_RishiSaintTerminal_MessagesSub
#. REC: TMLM:ITXT
msgctxt "000F6E"
msgid "Late payment?"
msgstr ""

#. List: 0
#. EDID: SFFL_Anchorpoint_RishiSaintTerminal_MessagesSub
#. REC: TMLM:UNAM
msgctxt "000F6F"
msgid "Subject: Still Waiting\nFrom: O. Cutler\n\nWhat's the status of that medical supplier you were lining up? You said it would all be taken care of a week ago. I've told you several times that our stocks are already dangerously low. It's getting to the point where I'm seriously considering shutting down the infirmary. If you don't want to see that happen, then you'd better find someone who can provide what I need, and soon.\n\n"
msgstr ""

