#. List: 0
#. EDID: SFFL_MS01_BabylonDrKim01_HackedTMLM
#. REC: TMLM:ITXT
msgctxt "000FB1"
msgid "Grace Kim's Personal Logs"
msgstr "그레이스 킴의 개인 일지"

#. List: 0
#. EDID: SFFL_MS01_BabylonDrKim01_HackedTMLM
#. REC: TMLM:UNAM
msgctxt "000FB2"
msgid "I've solicited everyone to submit a blood sample.\n\nZena - A+\nGrace - O+\nSasha - B-\nSunni - B+\nYeats - AB+\nIvica - ???\nCaspian - Rh-Null\nHal - A+\n\nIvica refuses to supply a sample which is ridiculous. I've insisted this is for the betterment of the outpost but he lets his pointless superstition take precedence over the safety of the group. \n\nIf god forbid Ivica needs a transfusion, I'd have to waste valuable time doing an antibody test first.\n\nBut the most interesting sample comes from Caspian, an extremely rare blood type which has no antigens in the Rh system. Statistically he's a unicorn -- even back on Earth there were only a handful of reported cases. I'd love to get a much larger sample but Ivica's rants have made him question the validity of my research and so far he's been reluctant to consent."
msgstr ""

#. List: 0
#. EDID: SFFL_MS01_BabylonDrKim01_HackedTMLM
#. REC: TMLM:ITXT
msgctxt "000FB3"
msgid "Outpost Blood Types "
msgstr ""

#. List: 0
#. EDID: SFFL_MS01_BabylonDrKim01_HackedTMLM
#. REC: TMLM:UNAM
msgctxt "000FB4"
msgid "I've been running tests on some of the local fauna that Hal's brought back as part of his hunts to see if they offer any clues.\n\nIt's hard to say without a control group, but it does seem like blood volume is less than what would be expected.\n\nI think I need to get more samples of blood from the people here. It's also a good idea to have ample reserves in the event a transfusion is necessary. I'll talk to Zena about having everyone in the group donate blood. "
msgstr ""

#. List: 0
#. EDID: SFFL_MS01_BabylonDrKim01_HackedTMLM
#. REC: TMLM:ITXT
msgctxt "000FB5"
msgid "Xenomorphic Study"
msgstr ""

#. List: 0
#. EDID: SFFL_MS01_BabylonDrKim01_HackedTMLM
#. REC: TMLM:UNAM
msgctxt "000FB6"
msgid "During pregnancy, the amount of blood in your body increases by about 20-30 percent, which increases the supply of iron and vitamins that the body needs to make hemoglobin. \n\nMy hypothesis is that something about the environment here affects the overall blood volume, which negates pregnancies. Caspian is the exception, albeit his mother was already pregnant when she arrived. Tests show he has a rare blood type, Rh-null. I wonder if that's the key?\n\nFrom a funding perspective, I can convince the suits the value of such a study. We need to know how birth rates are affected by the gravity, air composition, and food of this orbital.\n\nMy sources tell me there are many corporations looking to expand their operations by \"colonizing\" habitable planets. A practice which can be legally justified since they are not under the jurisdiction of any government."
msgstr ""

#. List: 0
#. EDID: SFFL_MS01_BabylonDrKim01_HackedTMLM
#. REC: TMLM:ITXT
msgctxt "000FB7"
msgid "Grant Proposal - Birth Rates and Blood Types"
msgstr ""

#. List: 0
#. EDID: SFFL_MS01_BabylonDrKim01_HackedTMLM
#. REC: TMLM:UNAM
msgctxt "000FB8"
msgid "New Babylon has been through a lot in the years before my arrival. The death of their leader, Alphonse Roberson (Caspian's father), and the mass exodus of half the citizens would have normally been a death sentence for the outpost.\n\nBut Zena's leadership has kept the ship afloat, somehow, someway. Yet the most interesting aspect of New Babylon from a research perspective relates to the conditions here and its effect on birth rates.\n\nMany of those who left in the exodus were couples. During their time here, not a single one was able to give birth to a child. Once they left the planet, they were able to grow their families quite extensively, according to my research."
msgstr ""

#. List: 0
#. EDID: SFFL_MS01_BabylonDrKim01_HackedTMLM
#. REC: TMLM:ITXT
msgctxt "000FB9"
msgid "New Babylon History"
msgstr ""

