#. List: 0
#. EDID: SFFL_SE_KT01_CaptainComputerEntry
#. REC: TMLM:UNAM
msgctxt "0019AA"
msgid "Last night I woke up to check on my sandwich and ran into this large, free-floating blob of water. It was absolutely disgusting.\n\nI panicked and shot it, and the blob split into dozen little pieces. Whatever it was, I think it's dead now, but we'll need a deep clean of the entire ship once we get to port."
msgstr ""

#. List: 0
#. EDID: SFFL_SE_KT01_CaptainComputerEntry
#. REC: TMLM:ITXT
msgctxt "0019AB"
msgid "Toxic blobs"
msgstr ""

#. List: 0
#. EDID: SFFL_SE_KT01_CaptainComputerEntry
#. REC: TMLM:UNAM
msgctxt "0019AC"
msgid "The crew has been pretty tense as of late, a combination of the long hours and sleepless nights. Sanderson threw a fit today about someone stealing his sandwich, and nearly went to blows with another crew member.\n\nThe sandwich is just a symptom of the larger problem -- we're just plain overworked. This team has survived spacers, pirates, and all manner of trouble, I'm not going to let a sandwich be the one that breaks us.\n\n"
msgstr ""

#. List: 0
#. EDID: SFFL_SE_KT01_CaptainComputerEntry
#. REC: TMLM:ITXT
msgctxt "0019AD"
msgid "Food Theft"
msgstr ""

#. List: 0
#. EDID: SFFL_SE_KT01_CaptainComputerEntry
#. REC: TMLM:UNAM
msgctxt "0019AE"
msgid "The habs have gotten extremely dirty as of late, and we're not sure why. I had the engineers check the filtration system, and they look clean, so it's not that.\n\nStill, it shouldn't affect the job. A little dust in our lungs isn't the worst thing."
msgstr ""

