#. List: 0
#. EDID: SFFL_Anchorpoint_SecurityTerminal_IncidentsSub
#. REC: TMLM:UNAM
msgctxt "0024AF"
msgid "Incident ID: 0341-X-933\nFiled by: C. Huang\n\nIncident Details:\n\nA group of 5 Crimson Fleet assailants initiated an armed confrontation shortly after embarking. Firefight ensued. Encounter was contained to main docking corridor area. Security personnel successfully repelled the attack, aided by Model S security bot designated \"Tiger.\"\n\nTwo of the attackers were killed, the other three suffered severe injuries and withdrew, Security personnel; suffered injuries, but no casualties\n\nUPDATE: The Crimson Fleet ship was found adrift in the Free Lanes, all hands deceased. It seems the three survivors of the failed attack ultimately succumbed to their injuries."
msgstr ""

#. List: 0
#. EDID: SFFL_Anchorpoint_SecurityTerminal_IncidentsSub
#. REC: TMLM:ITXT
msgctxt "0024B0"
msgid "0341-X-933"
msgstr ""

#. List: 0
#. EDID: SFFL_Anchorpoint_SecurityTerminal_IncidentsSub
#. REC: TMLM:UNAM
msgctxt "0024B1"
msgid "Incident ID: 0379-S-116\nFiled by: C. Huang\n\nIncident Details:\n\nComplaint filed by employee Maddie Wing. Plaintiff states that a patron, identified as L. Pancere, made unwanted advances and then followed her back to her private quarters in engineering section. Patron threatened to become violent, so Maddie ordered her security bot designated \"Tiger\" to attack. \n\nPatron suffered non-life-threatening injuries in the form of numerous lacerations and bruises and was taken to infirmary for treatment."
msgstr ""

#. List: 0
#. EDID: SFFL_Anchorpoint_SecurityTerminal_IncidentsSub
#. REC: TMLM:ITXT
msgctxt "0024B2"
msgid "0379-S-116"
msgstr ""

#. List: 0
#. EDID: SFFL_Anchorpoint_SecurityTerminal_IncidentsSub
#. REC: TMLM:UNAM
msgctxt "0024B3"
msgid "Incident ID: 0399-L-978\nFiled by: C. Corey\n\nIncident Details:\n\nAttempted property theft observed and reported by patron. Perpetrator. identified as J. Blades was seen leaving bar and entering personal bunks area, then emerging a short time later with full pockets. When confronted, the suspect produced several stolen items of marginal value. These were reclaimed.\n\nPerpetrator was forcibly removed from premises and warned not to return."
msgstr ""

#. List: 0
#. EDID: SFFL_Anchorpoint_SecurityTerminal_IncidentsSub
#. REC: TMLM:ITXT
msgctxt "0024B4"
msgid "0399-L-978"
msgstr ""

#. List: 0
#. EDID: SFFL_Anchorpoint_SecurityTerminal_IncidentsSub
#. REC: TMLM:UNAM
msgctxt "0024B5"
msgid "Incident ID: 0446-B-323\nFiled by: M. O'Keefe\n\nIncident Details:\n\nFight between two patrons, one of whom, identified as D. Castro, drew a knife and attempted to strike the other. Assailant was heavily inebriated, attack was therefore ineffective. Guards were able to subdue attacker and take weapon. Assailant was detained in cell for 2 days then released and banned from premises."
msgstr ""

#. List: 0
#. EDID: SFFL_Anchorpoint_SecurityTerminal_IncidentsSub
#. REC: TMLM:ITXT
msgctxt "0024B6"
msgid "0446-B-323"
msgstr ""

#. List: 0
#. EDID: SFFL_Anchorpoint_SecurityTerminal_IncidentsSub
#. REC: TMLM:UNAM
msgctxt "0024B7"
msgid "Incident ID: 0472-A-285\nFiled by: C. Corey\n\nIncident Details:\n\nDisturbance initiated by one member of a group of Spacers. Situation escalated into altercation involving multiple patrons. Spacers drew and fired weapons, injuring two. Security intervened and injured three of the spacers. \n\nNo fatalities resulted. Perpetrator who initiated the confrontation was taken into custody, the other Spacers departed, issuing threats. Spacers pledged to return in force.\n\n"
msgstr ""

#. List: 0
#. EDID: SFFL_Anchorpoint_SecurityTerminal_IncidentsSub
#. REC: TMLM:ITXT
msgctxt "0024B8"
msgid "0472-A-285"
msgstr ""

#. List: 0
#. EDID: SFFL_Anchorpoint_SecurityTerminal_IncidentsSub
#. REC: TMLM:FULL
msgctxt "0024B9"
msgid "Incident Reports"
msgstr ""

#. List: 0
#. EDID: SFFL_Anchorpoint_SecurityTerminal_MessagesSub
#. REC: TMLM:UNAM
msgctxt "0024BA"
msgid "Team,\n\nJust another reminder that you are all expected to be discreet, respectful and above all, mindful of the value we place on privacy here at Anchorpoint. \n\nWe are a security force with a duty to ensure the secure operation of the station, not to pry, eavesdrop or spy with intent to tip off the authorities in the United Colonies or Freestar Collective. And yes, I'm obviously aware there are those who would pay for such information.\n\nIf you can't handle this most vital responsibility, then you'll need to find employment elsewhere. This is not negotiable.\n\nPlease feel free to follow up with me if you have any questions or need clarification.\n\nThank you,\n\nR. Saint,\nProprietor\n"
msgstr ""

#. List: 0
#. EDID: SFFL_Anchorpoint_SecurityTerminal_MessagesSub
#. REC: TMLM:ITXT
msgctxt "0024BB"
msgid "Discretion is Key"
msgstr ""

#. List: 0
#. EDID: SFFL_Anchorpoint_SecurityTerminal_MessagesSub
#. REC: TMLM:UNAM
msgctxt "0024BC"
msgid "Staffing Update\n\nI promised I'd provide an update when I have one, so here it is.\n\nAs you know, I met with Mister Saint to discuss staffing. Specifically, I requested that we add two additional positions as the first step in a phased expansion program of our security personnel.\n\nAt this time, Mister Saint feels that our limited force has proven more than capable of handling the threats we face. While we should all be proud to have engendered such confidence, I'm well aware that we are stretched about as thin as can be. \n\nRest assured, I'll continue to press the issue. I know how important this is to everyone.\n\nThanks for your patience.\n\n-Chan\n"
msgstr ""

#. List: 0
#. EDID: SFFL_Anchorpoint_SecurityTerminal_MessagesSub
#. REC: TMLM:ITXT
msgctxt "0024BD"
msgid "Staffing Update"
msgstr ""

#. List: 0
#. EDID: SFFL_Anchorpoint_SecurityTerminal_MessagesSub
#. REC: TMLM:UNAM
msgctxt "0024BE"
msgid "Now that we've said goodbye to our former colleague Mason, I wanted to clear the air about the reason for his abrupt departure. \n\nIn a recent conversation with Maddie, I was made aware that Tiger suffered a brief glitch in his programming that caused him to briefly act in an aggressive manner toward Mason, who was walking through the engineering area at the time. \n\nAs Maddie explained it, the robot growled and crouched low, as if about to launch a close-range attack. No attack took place and the moment passed. \n\nUnfortunately, Mason drew his firearm and took two shots at Tiger in what I can only describe as a moment of panic. One of these ricocheted into a nearby piece of machinery and caused damage. Luckily, it was not a vital system, but it could have been.\n\nSuch behavior is unprofessional and simply not up to our standards. As such, Mason was relieved of his position and escorted off the station.\n\n-Chan\n"
msgstr ""

#. List: 0
#. EDID: SFFL_Anchorpoint_SecurityTerminal_MessagesSub
#. REC: TMLM:ITXT
msgctxt "0024BF"
msgid "Mason's Departure"
msgstr ""

