msgid "Ban List"
msgstr ""

#. List: 0
#. EDID: SFFL_Anchorpoint_SecurityTerminal_BanSub
#. REC: TMLM:UNAM
msgctxt "002503"
msgid "Team,\n\nJust another reminder that you are all expected to be discreet, respectful and above all, mindful of the value we place on privacy here at Anchorpoint. \n\nWe are a security force with a duty to ensure the secure operation of the station, not to pry, eavesdrop or spy with intent to tip off the authorities in the United Colonies or Freestar Collective. And yes, I'm obviously aware there are those who would pay for such information.\n\nIf you can't handle this most vital responsibility, then you'll need to find employment elsewhere. This is not negotiable.\n\nPlease feel free to follow up with me if you have any questions or need clarification.\n\nThank you,\n\nR. Saint,\nProprietor\n"
msgstr ""

#. List: 0
#. EDID: SFFL_Anchorpoint_SecurityTerminal_BanSub
#. REC: TMLM:ITXT
msgctxt "002504"
msgid "Discretion is Key"
msgstr ""

#. List: 0
#. EDID: SFFL_Anchorpoint_SecurityTerminal_BanSub
#. REC: TMLM:UNAM
msgctxt "002505"
msgid "Staffing Update\n\nO promised I'd provide an update when I have one, so here it is.\n\nAs you know, I met with Mister Saint to discuss staffing. Specifically, I requested that we add two additional positions as the first step in a phased expansion program of our security personnel.\n\nAt this time, Mister Saint feels that our limited force has proven more than capable of handling the threats we face. While we should all be proud to have engendered such confidence, I'm well aware that we are stretched about as thin as can be. \n\nRest assured, I'll continue to press the issue. I know how important this is to everyone.\n\nThanks for your patience.\n\n-Chan\n"
msgstr ""

#. List: 0
#. EDID: SFFL_Anchorpoint_SecurityTerminal_BanSub
#. REC: TMLM:ITXT
msgctxt "002506"
msgid "Staffing Update"
msgstr ""

#. List: 0
#. EDID: SFFL_Anchorpoint_SecurityTerminal_BanSub
#. REC: TMLM:UNAM
msgctxt "002507"
msgid "Now that we've said goodbye to our former colleague Mason, I wanted to clear the air about the reason for his abrupt departure. \n\nIn a recent conversation with Maddie, I was made aware that Tiger suffered a brief glitch in his programming that caused him to briefly act in an aggressive manner toward Mason, who was walking through the engineering area at the time. \n\nAs Maddie explained it, the robot growled and crouched low, as if about to launch a close-range attack. No attack took place and the moment passed. \n\nUnfortunately, Mason drew his firearm and took two shots at Tiger in what I can only describe as a moment of panic. One of these ricocheted into a nearby piece of machinery and caused damage. Luckily, it was not a vital system, but it could have been.\n\nSuch behavior is unprofessional and simply not up to our standards. As such, Mason was relieved of his position and escorted off the station.\n"
msgstr ""

#. List: 0
#. EDID: SFFL_Anchorpoint_SecurityTerminal_BanSub
#. REC: TMLM:ITXT
msgctxt "002508"
msgid "Mason's Departure"
msgstr ""

