#. List: 1
#. EDID: SFFL_MS01_Quest
#. REC: QUST:CNAM
msgctxt "00093B"
msgid "A man named Bernhard told me about a refugee camp that was left to starve by a pirate named Caruso. I should go to the camp and investigate what happened."
msgstr ""

#. List: 1
#. EDID: SFFL_MS01_ShinarAudioSlate01
#. REC: BOOK:DESC
msgctxt "000942"
msgid "Sheila Costas: What do you think about this refugee, Caruso?\n\nBernhard Kleiber: Quiet man, hard worker. Keeps to himself mostly.\n\nSheila Costas: I mean, his ship didn't look like it was built for trade.\n\nAnd some of the details of his story don't add up. \n\nBernhard Kleiber: You think he's a smuggler?\n\nSheila Costas: I think he's worse. \n\nBernhard Kleiber: Relax. Even if you're right, the man can barely stand. He's no threat to the outpost.\n\nSheila Costas: At the very least, we should lock him up, treat him like a prisoner.\n\nBernhard Kleiber: Well, you'll have to take it up with the group. But I think you're overreacting."
msgstr ""

#. List: 1
#. EDID: SFFL_MS01_ShinarAudioSlate02
#. REC: BOOK:DESC
msgctxt "000944"
msgid "Bernhard Kleiber: What's happening? What's wrong?\n\nSheila Costas: It's Caruso. He's taken everything. The ship, our supplies...\n\nBernhard Kleiber: What about the food storage? The water?\n\nSheila Costas: It's gone, Bernhard. All of it.\n\nBernhard Kleiber: When is the next supply run? Home base will notice if we don't check in.\n\nSheila Costas: We won't get a re-supply in time. He waited until we restocked before making his move.\n\nDon't you see? There is no way out from this.\n\nBernhard Kleiber: No. We will find a way to survive. Trust me. We will.\n\n"
msgstr ""

#. List: 1
#. EDID: SFFL_MS01_ShinarAudioSlate03
#. REC: BOOK:DESC
msgctxt "000946"
msgid "It's been three days since we were left for dead. A few went out in search of food and water, but haven't returned.\n\nDehydration symptoms have started to set in for all of us. Fatigue, dizziness...\n\nI recognize that outside of a miracle, this is likely my last will and testament.\n\nThere is only one choice left. The others are already discussing how to do it.\n\n\n"
msgstr ""

#. List: 1
#. EDID: SFFL_MS01_RelaxationTape02
#. REC: BOOK:DESC
msgctxt "000948"
msgid "Welcome back.\n\nIn life, we find it hard to be present. But presently, you are here. Uncluttered. Unobstructed. Unbothered. \n\nHere in this zero space, your mind is clear. You notice you are standing on something. A cube. No, not a cube, a Chunk.\n\nYou drop to your knees. You take a bite of the ground. It's familiar, and soothing. It's pork. But if you dislike pork, it's not that. Really, it's your favorite food. It's comfort for your soul. \n\nYou lie down on the chunk of not pork, and find yourself in perfect harmony with the universe. For the Chunk is now part of you, and you are the Chunk.\n\nJust as we are all made of stars, we are all made of Chunks."
msgstr ""
"돌아오신 것을 환영합니다.\n"
"\n"
"살면서 '지금 이 순간'에 집중하기는 어렵습니다. 하지만 지금, 당신은 여기에 있습니다. 거리낄 것 없이. 방해받을 것 없이. 신경 쓸 "
"것 없이.\n"
"\n"
"이 제로의 공간에서 당신의 마음은 맑아집니다. 문득 무언가 위에 서 있다는 것을 깨닫습니다. 큐브로군요. 아니네요. 큐브가 아니라 "
"청크입니다.\n"
"\n"
"무릎을 꿇고 땅을 한 입 베어 물어봅니다. 익숙하고 편안한 맛이로군요. 돼지고기입니다. 돼지고기를 싫어하신다면, 다른 맛이겠죠. 진정으로 "
"당신이 가장 좋아하는 음식의 맛 말이지요. 영혼의 위안을 주는 맛입니다.\n"
"\n"
"돼지고기가 아닌 청크 위에 눕자, 우주와 완벽하게 하나가 됩니다. 이제 청크는 당신의 일부고, 당신은 곧 청크입니다.\n"
"\n"
"우리 모두가 별에서 왔듯이, 우리 모두는 청크로 이루어져 있습니다."

#. List: 1
#. EDID: SFFL_MS01_ShinarYeatsSlate01
#. REC: BOOK:DESC
msgctxt "00095B"
msgid "I've long been a fan of the good book, and the mythology of old. Take the story of Babylon, for example.\n\nIn Hebrew, Babylon (Babel) means confusion, but in the ancient Akkadian text it appears as \"Bab-ilani\" or \"gate of the gods.\" \n\nWhen I chose a place to spread the gospel, the name New Babylon struck a chord. If it's truly a \"gate of the gods,\" perhaps here is where I would be closer to His word. And while living in a remote settlement is undoubtedly strange, my path to preaching was never a straight and narrow one.\n\nIt was twisting and wide and full of potholes. I believe this is not a sin, however. Some would accuse me of being unholy, because I choose a drop of liquor here and a pint there. They see the libelous blood in my cheeks and claim there is not a shred of divinity in me.\n\nAnd while it's true I have not held congress with God and recently have barely sought the company of soap, I feel I am still on the right one, when paths are considered.\n\nThe road feels comfortable under my feet.\n"
msgstr ""
"예전부터 나는 성경과 고대 신화를 좋아했다. 예를 들어 바빌론 이야기 같은 것 말이다.\n"
"\n"
"히브리어에서 바빌론(바벨)은 혼란을 뜻하지만, 고대 아카드어로는 \"밥-일라니(Bab-ilani)\" 또는 \"신들의 문\"이라 표기된다."
"\n"
"\n"
"복음을 전할 곳을 고를 때, 뉴바빌론이라는 이름이 마음에 와닿았다. 정말로 신들의 문이라면, 이곳에서 그분의 말씀에 더 가까워질 수 "
"있으리라. 외진 정착지에서 사는 것은 분명 기이하지만, 설교의 길은 원래 순탄하거나 편안한 적이 없었다.\n"
"\n"
"구불구불 막연한 길에 구덩이투성이였다. 하지만 이것이 죄값을 치르는 건 아니라고 생각한다. 여기저기서 술을 한 잔씩 마신다고 불경하다 "
"비난하는 자들도 있겠지. 뺨에 떠오른 모욕의 붉은빛을 보며 내게는 신성의 조각도 없다고 말할 거다.\n"
"\n"
"신과 깊은 대화를 나눈 지도 오래됐고, 솔직히 말해 요즘은 비누로 씻는 일조차 거의 없지만, 그래도 삶의 여러 방향을 놓고 본다면 나는 "
"여전히 옳은 길 을 가고 있는 것 같다.\n"
"\n"
"발밑의 길이 편안하다.\n"

#. List: 1
#. EDID: SFFL_MS01_ShinarYeatsSlate02
#. REC: BOOK:DESC
msgctxt "00095D"
msgid "I've arrived at this place but so far have found few ears willing to lend themselves to my sermon.\n\nI hoped maybe it was the atmosphere. Perhaps sound is muffled on this planet, or its people suffering from an earwax epidemic, but I was not so lucky. Worse yet, the conditions are miserable and the conversation moreso.\n\nDr. Kim assures me they are happy and healthy and existing just fine sans religious guidance. If so, then what is my purpose here? Is this not the gate of the gods? \n\nI am waiting, maker. It's your move. Until then, I will be at the bar, having a drink."
msgstr ""
"이곳에 도착하긴 했지만, 아직까지 내 설교에 귀를 기울이는 사람은 거의 없다.\n"
"\n"
"분위기 탓이길 바랐다. 이 행성에서는 소리가 먹먹하게 들리는 건 아닐까, 아니면 귀지가 끼는 유행병이라도 도는 건 아닐까 기대해 봤지만, "
"그런 행운은 없었다. 게다가 생활 환경은 비참하고, 대화는 더 비참하다.\n"
"\n"
"킴 박사는 주민들은 행복하고 건강하며 종교적 지도 없이도 잘 지내고 있다고 장담한다. 그렇다면 나는 여기서 무엇을 해야 하는 걸까? "
"이곳은 신들의 문이 아니란 말인가?\n"
"\n"
"기다리겠습니다. 창조주여. 당신 차례입니다. 그때까지 저는 바에서 한잔 하고 있으렵니다."

