#. REC: BOOK:DESC
msgctxt "000E38"
msgid "Emmett,\n\nI'm reaching out to see if you have any security connections beyond our typical vendors. I know our budget is already tight as it is, but these turrets they provided are broken down more often than operational.\n\nLook. If we need to reach out to the Ecliptic, I'm okay with it. Anything will have to do.\n\n- John"
msgstr ""

#. List: 1
#. EDID: SFBGS00DDR009_Slate04
#. REC: BOOK:DESC
msgctxt "000E3A"
msgid "No matter what, you can't let Bill near any of the supplies. I provided you a new key that I also will have a copy of on me. I left it in one of your desk cabinets. Use it from now on and make sure to always lock the gates behind you."
msgstr ""

#. List: 1
#. EDID: SFFL_Anchorpoint_TextSlate_BriceMessage
#. REC: BOOK:DESC
msgctxt "000E3C"
msgid "Mister Brice,\n\nAccompanying this slate is a CredStik with payment for the latest delivery. Our endeavor has demonstrated promising results, and we intend to expand production. This means our need for your services will soon increase. \n\nIf you can expand your operation sufficiently to provide double the current volume, we'll be happy to continue working with you as our sole contractor. If not, rest assured, we'll continue what has been an agreeable partnership, though we will need to expand our sourcing. The opportunity is yours if you want it.\n\nWe look forward to your reply"
msgstr ""

#. List: 1
#. EDID: SFFL_SE_EC03_Keepsake_Dataslate
#. REC: BOOK:DESC
msgctxt "000E3E"
msgid "3 THINGS ABOUT MY MUM\nby Anjali Lau-Kazan, 8\n\nMy mother is very strong and brave. Once upon a time she was on a navy ship that hunted pirates. That's where she met dad!! One day I will have my own ship, and paint it all black so pirates can't see me.\n\nMy mother is very wise. When she speaks you better listen because it's important! There are many examples but I'm too tired to write them now.\n\nMy mother loves me more than everything, even dad. Dad always looks grumpy, but that's because of his condition. He loves me more than everything too.\n\nI love my parents and I LOVE MY MUM!!\n\n  _ _\n|   `  |\n \\    /\n   \\/\n\nHAPPY MOTHERS DAY MUM"
msgstr ""

#. List: 1
#. EDID: SFBGS00DDR005_Slate04
#. REC: BOOK:DESC
msgctxt "000E42"
msgid "Since our Ecliptic \"friends\" have joined us, I've had to keep a closer hold of our valuables, which includes the keys. \n\nThe master key for our exit door out the cave will be moved to our closed off quarters. Please grab and leave that key on the holder in our work area. KEEP IT CLOSE as that is our only copy of that key and I do not want it falling in the hands of a delinquent Ecliptic.\n\nAs for the weapon stash key, that will be on me AT ALL TIMES for the same reasons. To not rustle feathers with the mercenaries, I left our weapons out there but they will be locked. I'll also keep a watchful eye on them."
msgstr ""

#. List: 1
#. EDID: SFFL_SE01_DataSlate03
#. REC: BOOK:DESC
msgctxt "000E44"
msgid "An interesting thing happened last night. A lone, spacefaring grandmother invited me onto her ship for a spot of food and company. I must be crazy because I took her up on her offer. \n\nShe was pleasant enough, and it was nice to be able to speak with someone who's around my own age for a change. We ate, drank, and laughed about the odds of two old women meeting each other in the vastness of space. \n\nShe told me her grandkids aren't too happy with her doing what she's doing. Guess she doesn't know how lucky she is. I was never lucky in love, so I don't have any grandkids - or family, really - to worry about, or to worry about me. It gets lonely out here. \n\nIt all got me thinking: what other interesting people are out there? Maybe I should follow her example and start inviting people on board. \n"
msgstr ""

#. List: 1
#. EDID: SFFL_R03_DataSlate01
#. REC: BOOK:DESC
msgctxt "000E46"
msgid "Thanks for coming to speak with me face to face. I appreciate the due respect, and I like to see that you're not a coward. I don't like working with cowards. But, I also don't like working with failures.\n\nYou're not hitting your quota. I need ships. That's what I pay you for. I pay you, and you get me ships. It's that simple. But you haven't been delivering for a long time, and you know that, don't you? Sure you do - you're not stupid, you're just incompetent - and no amount of smooth talking from you changes the fact that you aren't delivering. \n\nLook, I like you, so I hate to say this, but you're expendable. I'm running a business here, and this is your final shot. If you screw up on this run, you're done. I'm sure you know what I mean by that. \n\n-- D"
msgstr ""

#. List: 1
#. EDID: SFFL_MS01_SunniSlate_Rusty
#. REC: BOOK:DESC
msgctxt "000E4A"
msgid "Potential Names for Robot [DO NOT STEAL!!!!]\nby Sunni Kim\n\n[] Model A-Hole\n[] Farmer Charmer\n[] Gary\n[] It Just Works\n[] Takahashi\n[] K.R.I.S - Killer Robot and Industrial Servant\n[X] Rusty"
msgstr ""

#. List: 1
#. EDID: SFFL_Anchorpoint_TextSlate_DrinkIdeas
#. REC: BOOK:DESC
msgctxt "000E4C"
msgid "New drink ideas for the bar\n\nSTAR SAILOR\nI've been wanting to do a nautical themed drink forever. We're at \"Anchor\"point after all! Should be in the blue/green color range.\n\nFREE LANE FLAME\nI've been asked a couple of times if we have anything spicy, so this would incorporate hot sauce. What kind of base goes with hot sauce? Tomato juice maybe? Can we get that?\n\nSAINT'S BLESSING\nShamelessly sucking up to the boss here. Should be clear, for saintly purity.\n\nTIGER STRIPE\nMaddie's idea so I'm not completely married to it, but it could work. I envision a colorful liquor blend with bold tones, really eye-catching. Uses liquors of different densities. Something with an orange color and a dark color. Will be a challenge to pour but look very unique. Good opportunity for a high cost item!\n\nVAL'S VODKA SURPRISE\nHad to name at least ONE drink after myself, right? The surprise part will be whatever cheap liquor we're trying to get rid of.\n\nTHE ANCHOR PINT\nBeer but served in a special custom pint glass. We can sell these at a premium. That's assuming we can find someone to create and ship custom pint glasses without it costing a fortune."
msgstr ""

