#. List: 1
#. EDID: SFBGS00DDR009_Slate05
#. REC: BOOK:DESC
msgctxt "001467"
msgid "Seriously? You couldn't let me get my laundry out before putting in yours?\n\nAt least put it in a basket. Not on the dirty ass floor. Had to wash my clothes again in the middle of the night."
msgstr ""

#. List: 1
#. EDID: SFFL_SE_KT01_Note
#. REC: BOOK:DESC
msgctxt "001469"
msgid "The rest of the crew are always taking my food and I'm tired of it. \n\nI literally put a note on the sandwich saying SANDERSON'S PROPERTY - DO NOT EAT but it seems there's an illiteracy epidemic going around, because someone took a bite out of the sandwich and put it back. Put it back! WHO DOES THAT? \n\nWorse yet, who knows how many crumbs and flecks of cheese are just floating around the ship. As someone who values tidiness, this is UNACCEPTABLE.\n\nSo far no one has come forward. They say I'm overreacting. Well, whoever this sandwich terrorist is, they're not getting the rest of it.\n\nI'm putting it away in the Captain's locker where it's safe.\n"
msgstr ""

#. List: 1
#. EDID: SFFL_MS01_SunniSlate
#. REC: BOOK:DESC
msgctxt "00146D"
msgid "Man, Grace wasn't kidding when she called this place a dump. \n\nNo, I think that's an insult to dumps. This is what you get when a dump eats like thirty burritos from some shady food truck, and then drops a bomb in the toilet, and then that bomb marries a sack of rotting milk sitting in the sun for a month and they have a baby.\n\nI don't know how Grace does it, to be frank. That's why she's little miss perfect, been that way since we were diaper dandies.\n\nEveryone here's so UPTIGHT too. Bunch of wind-up toys. Sasha's cute though. It's a shame she probably finds my existence political."
msgstr ""

#. List: 1
#. EDID: SFFL_SE01_DataSlate01
#. REC: BOOK:DESC
msgctxt "00146F"
msgid "Something is wrong with me. I'm old, but these aren't just normal aches and pains. Something is inside of me, I know it.\n\nI shouldn't have eaten that visitor's food -- it went bad, or something was wrong with it. Must've been infested with parasites because I've never felt like this before, like I'm losing control of my own body. \n\nI want to land and get help but I can't. It's like my body isn't listening to my brain, or maybe it's the other way around? Nothing feels normal. And these headaches... nothing is helping. What the hell is wrong with me?\n\nAnd the itching... I'm about ready to rip the skin off my bones. God, we're so itchy.\n\n"
msgstr ""

