#. List: 1
#. EDID: SFFL_Anchorpoint_AudioSlate_FinalReport
#. REC: BOOK:DESC
msgctxt "001941"
msgid "Gus Gentry: Don't know why I'm recording this. Just seems like somebody should say something. You live in a place long enough, it starts to feel like a kind of home, I suppose. I remember the day we started construction on this station. There was so much enthusiasm, so much pride. A whole lot of folks put a whole lot of passion into the job. We built her right, and built her to last. And now, it's time to say goodbye. Without the occasional correction from the orbital thrusters, she'll start to drop. Until one day, she'll light up the sky over Algorab II in a last, glorious fireball. Damn... wish I could be there to see it. This is Chief Engineer Gus Gentry of Anchorpoint Station, signing off for the last time."
msgstr ""

#. List: 1
#. EDID: SFFL_BE_RS03_DataSlate02
#. REC: BOOK:DESC
msgctxt "001943"
msgid "We thought it was dormant. Just some ancient inert thing. \n\nWhen I ordered Ruiz and Dellen to open the containment seal to scan for contamination... it twitched.\n\nWe ran tests. We shouldn't have gone anywhere near it. Should have left it buried on that damn moon.\n\nNow, it's... inside everything.\n\n"
msgstr ""

#. List: 1
#. EDID: SFFL_MS01_RelaxationTape03
#. REC: BOOK:DESC
msgctxt "001947"
msgid "Welcome back.\n\nBy now, you are fully relaxed, in a blissful, restful state. If you're wondering if your slate is broken, don't worry. Due to budget cuts audio will no longer be provided. But that's okay.\n\nInstead I want you to imagine you are hearing my voice, over soothing, relaxing music. To get an idea of what my voice sounds like, you need only listen to a previous tape, then return.\n\nAre you back? Good.\n\nTake a deep breath. Picture in your mind an apple. It's ripe, crisp, with a bead of water glistening from its skin. There's only one thing wrong with it. The shape. If only it had sharp, well-defined edges. Like a Chunk.\n\nYou may still find your thoughts wandering. That's all right. Acknowledge them. They may be saying \"Apples shouldn't be square!\" But those thoughts are mistaken, born from an angry, tense mind. They are not your concern. Let them roll away, like Chunks do, down the chute of a vending machine, right into your hand.\n\nPick up that Chunk, and take a bite. Let its refreshing, synthetically engineered taste flow through your insides. As you relax, deeper and deeper, you curl up into a cube. As you curl, you find yourself mimicking that cubic apple. Transform the curves of your body into a healthy, symmetrical cube.\n\nLook at yourself. You've done it. You've reached your final form. Nothing can harm you. You are perfect. You are a Chunk."
msgstr ""
"돌아오신 것을 환영합니다.\n"
"\n"
"이제 완전히 이완된, 더없이 행복한 안식 상태에 계실 겁니다. 혹시 슬레이트가 고장인가 싶으시다면 걱정 마세요. 예산 삭감으로 더 이상 "
"음성이 제공되지 않습니다. 하지만 괜찮습니다.\n"
"\n"
"대신 제 목소리가 편안하고 느긋한 음악의 선율 위를 흐르는 모습을 상상해 보세요. 제 목소리가 어떤지 알고 싶으시다면, 이전 테이프를 "
"다시 한번 들어보시면 됩니다.\n"
"\n"
"들어보셨나요? 좋습니다.\n"
"\n"
"깊이 숨을 들이쉬세요. 마음속에 사과 한 알을 떠올려 보세요. 잘 익었고, 아삭하고, 껍질에 물방울이 반짝이고 있습니다. 한 가지 아쉬운 "
"점이 있다면 바로 모양입니다. 날카롭고 또렷한 모서리가 있다면 좋을 텐데 말이죠. 청크처럼요.\n"
"\n"
"아직 생각이 흔들릴 수도 있습니다. 괜찮습니다. 인정하세요. \"사과가 네모날 리 없잖아!\"라고 생각할 수도 있습니다. 하지만 그런 "
"생각은 화나고 긴장된 마음에서 비롯된 오류입니다. 그런 건 신경 쓸 필요 없습니다. 자판기에서 굴러 내려와 손에 쏙 들어오는 청크처럼, "
"흘려보내세요.\n"
"\n"
"청크를 집어 한 입 베어 무세요. 상쾌하고 합성된 맛이 몸속으로 퍼지게 하세요. 몸이 점점 더 깊이 이완되면서 큐브 안으로 둥글게 "
"말립니다. 그러다 네모난 사과를 닮아가고 있음을 깨닫습니다. 몸의 곡선을 건강하고 대칭적인 큐브처럼 변신시키세요.\n"
"\n"
"자신을 돌아 보세요. 해냈습니다. 최종 형태에 도달했습니다. 어떤 것도 당신을 해칠 수 없습니다. 당신은 완벽합니다. 당신이 곧 "
"청크입니다."

