#. List: 1
#. EDID: SFBGS00DDR018_HumanHostileNote
#. REC: BOOK:DESC
msgctxt "00194B"
msgid "Today's the big day!\nI'm going to try \"The Ultimate Team Trustfall\" I've been working on. I'll stand at the edge of the tower and gracefully fall backwards into my team's waiting arms. I can't wait to see how the others react - they'll definitely respect me after this...\n\n(Remember: Say something inspiring as I fall.)\n\n"
msgstr ""

#. List: 1
#. EDID: SFFL_MS02_OpalsNote
#. REC: BOOK:DESC
msgctxt "00194E"
msgid "Man, I had to step out for a minute. I swear, if I don't talk about this or get this out or something, I'm gonna explode. I cannot keep this in if I'm gonna be drinking.\nI don't get why Sadie has to bring her sister to everything she's invited to. Sure, help her socialize more, but she doesn't do or say anything at these parties.\nAll she does is stand in a corner like some sad, lost child. It's so annoying. I liked her better when she was sick. At least then she wasn't taking up space.\nCoop's nice cause, yeah, he's quiet, but he doesn't look sad or anything. Wren makes me sad. She makes everyone sad. I just don't get why she's always around.\nOkay. I better head back out. Not like I can stay in the cockpit the whole time. What a bitch..."
msgstr ""

#. List: 1
#. EDID: SFFL_Anchorpoint_AudioSlate_Interview
#. REC: BOOK:DESC
msgctxt "001951"
msgid "Evan Alonso: Excuse me, Ms. LeBlanc? Just a few quick questions for SSNN, if you could.\n\nGabriella LeBlanc: Very well, but make it quick.\n\nEvan Alonso: Anchorpoint was built on the premise that Grav Drive technology will advance beyond its current limits. If it doesn't, is there a fallback plan? Some other way to use the station that's profitable?\n\nGabriella LeBlanc: *Chuckle* I hardly think that's necessary. As someone who's spent her entire professional life in the world of commerce, I can promise you one thing. Progress is inevitable, especially if there's a profit to be made.\n\nEvan Alonso: Some have characterized Anchorpoint as a vanity project. They point to the personal wealth you've sunk into it, and the speculative nature of the venture. Do you feel like that's an unfair characterization? Any words for the skeptics?\n\nGabriella LeBlanc: I welcome it. Throughout our history, every visionary has had skeptics. It's a simple truth that bold ideas elicit strong reactions. I assure you,we're going into this with clear eyes and a great plan.\n\nEvan Alonso: One more if I may...\n\nGabriella LeBlanc: I'm sorry, but I really don't have the time. My press agent can handle any further inquiries.\n\nEvan Alonso: Thanks for your time.\n\n"
msgstr ""

