#. REC: MESG:DESC
msgctxt "0019F4"
msgid "You can now use Cruise Mode to explore the Free Lanes, the space between planets in a solar system.\n\nEnter and exit Cruise Mode by holding [Cruise] while in space. Adjust speed with the throttle. Use [Boosters] to accelerate to maximum Cruise speeds quickly.\n\nCruise will automatically disengage when arriving at Free Lanes encounters, but not at Planets or Moons.\n\nEngage Autopilot to automatically navigate and arrive at any location.\n\n\n"
msgstr ""

#. List: 1
#. EDID: HelpFreeLanesCruiseModePC
#. REC: MESG:DESC
msgctxt "0019F7"
msgid "Cruise Mode allows you to fly your ship anywhere within a star system without using Fast Travel. The space between planets is referred to as \"the Free Lanes.\" Cruise Mode cannot fly between Star Systems however, only the Grav Drive can do this. \n\nEnter and exit Cruise Mode by holding [Cruise] while in space. Adjust speed with the throttle. Use [Boosters] to accelerate to maximum Cruise speeds quickly. \n\nCruise Mode uses different ranges of speed noted by bars at the edge of your ship HUD. Your ship may automatically adjust the Cruise speed range as you approach locations in space for better control.\n\nYour ship will automatically disengage Cruise Mode when arriving at Free Lanes encounters, but not at Planets or Moons. Manually exit Cruise Mode near Planets or Moons to arrive at them, or engage Autopilot to automatically navigate and arrive at any location.\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n"
msgstr ""

