#. List: 1
#. EDID: SFFL_BE_RS03_DataSlate01
#. REC: BOOK:DESC
msgctxt "001EBB"
msgid "Nights are getting worse. I'm seeing things. I thought I saw Meryl standing over me last night - but Meryl's been gone for two months. The whispering won't stop. Coming from the vents, from the walls... or maybe it's just in my own head.\n \nI begged the captain. Told him we had to jettison the container. Said we could mark it as \"lost in transfer,\" no one would question it.\n\nHe just shook his head. \"Corporate orders.\"\n\nGod I don't want to die out here.\n\n"
msgstr ""

#. List: 1
#. EDID: SFFL_SE04_DataSlate01
#. REC: BOOK:DESC
msgctxt "001EBD"
msgid "The engine is out again. Engineering said they fixed it but these \"repairs\" are just burning through our supplies. \n\nMedications are dwindling, rations even more so. Morale is in the garbage and dropping more every day. Not sure how much longer we can hold out before I have a mutiny on my hands."
msgstr ""

#. List: 1
#. EDID: SFFL_SE01_DataSlate02
#. REC: BOOK:DESC
msgctxt "001EBF"
msgid "This body is itchy. Itchy, scratchy. Too old. \n\nHead is itchy. Brain, eyes are itchy. \n\nNeed it to stop make the itch stop\n\nitchy itchy itchy itchy itchy\n"
msgstr ""

#. List: 1
#. EDID: SFFL_Anchorpoint_TextSlate_MaddiesList
#. REC: BOOK:DESC
msgctxt "001EC1"
msgid "TO DO\n\n- Check air filters\n- Duct inspection\n- Replace coolant in bar freezer\n- Firmware update for gambling machines\n- Replace rusted bolts on docking collar\n- Refuel stationkeeping thruster four\n- Seal crack on infirmary toilet bowl\n"
msgstr ""

#. List: 1
#. EDID: SFFL_Anchorpoint_TextSlate_RishiPSA
#. REC: BOOK:DESC
msgctxt "001EC3"
msgid "Dear Patrons,\n\nPlease allow me to express my sincere apologies for the unfortunate incident that took place in the bar. My staff and I take great pride in opening our doors to anyone who wishes to enjoy a drink, a good conversation or the chance to conduct some business here in our unique establishment, but that open-mindedness also comes with risks.\n\nDespite what you might have heard, no serious injuries were suffered. Rest assured, we have detained the individual responsible. As for the rest of the unruly guests, they wisely opted to leave. I know they issued some alarming threats, but frankly, we hear those quite often around here, and they never amount to anything.\n\nIf, however, the Spacers choose to come back looking for trouble, our courageous, expertly-trained security force will be ready.\n\nThank you for your understanding,\n\nRishi Saint, Owner and Proprietor"
msgstr ""

#. List: 1
#. EDID: SFBGS00DDR009_Slate06
#. REC: BOOK:DESC
msgctxt "001EC5"
msgid "If you're reading this, please put the weights back after using them. If you can't lift the weight back, then don't use them!\n\nAnd who the hell is leaving their sweat all over the bench and equipment? Why are the dumbbells soaking!? That is so disgusting and should be a damn war crime. We have rags for a reason."
msgstr ""

#. List: 1
#. EDID: SFFL_MS01_Note_ExtraVote
#. REC: BOOK:DESC
msgctxt "001EC7"
msgid "[ ] Execution - Death for Hal Caruso\n\n[x] Exonerate - Absolve Hal Caruso of his past crimes\n\n[ ] Exile - Hal Caruso will leave New Babylon and never return\n"
msgstr ""

#. List: 1
#. EDID: SFFL_Z01_Slate2
#. REC: BOOK:DESC
msgctxt "001ECA"
msgid "So, this is what it all led to, hm? I'll be out of air soon and I haven't seen anyone for the past... I don't know anymore. \nI should have listened to her. Begged for me to get a job on land. Happy wife, happy life, right? But the pay- It's real helpful now. I guess I hoped if we had enough we could have grown gray in peace. Perfect life and all that. But now...\nI just want to be in it a bit longer... \nI'm so tired.\n"
msgstr ""

#. List: 1
#. EDID: SFFL_SE_EC01_Book_MobyDick_m
#. REC: BOOK:DESC
msgctxt "001ECE"
msgid "CHAPTER 1. Loomings.\n\nCall me Ishmael. Some years ago - never mind how long precisely - having little or no money in my purse, and nothing particular to interest me on shore, I thought I would sail about a little and see the watery part of the world. It is a way I have of driving off the spleen and regulating the circulation. Whenever I find myself growing grim about the mouth; whenever it is a damp, drizzly November in my soul; whenever I find myself involuntarily pausing before coffin warehouses, and bringing up the rear of every funeral I meet; and especially whenever my hypos get such an upper hand of me, that it requires a strong moral principle to prevent me from deliberately stepping into the street, and methodically knocking people's hats off - then, I account it high time to get to sea as soon as I can. This is my substitute for pistol and ball. With a philosophical flourish Cato throws himself upon his sword; I quietly take to the ship. There is nothing surprising in this. If they but knew it, almost all men in their degree, some time or other, cherish very nearly the same feelings towards the ocean with me.\n\n[And so continues Melville's classic tale of revenge and obsession, for a total of 341 pages.]"
msgstr ""

#. List: 1
#. EDID: StarbornContainerSlate
#. REC: BOOK:DESC
msgctxt "001ED0"
msgid "I apologize for the secrecy, but I was asked to reveal this only to you.\n\nI was given the schematic for a Quantum Entanglement Device - at least that's what it's called in the plan. The device should generate a Quantum Entanglement Field which serves as a container of sorts. The plan says the device and any items placed inside will exist in ALL spacetime.\n\nNo one is sure what will happen once you jump to the Unity, but I have a feeling this will keep any important items safe. The capacity is limited, but you can also feed it Quantum Essence to expand its capacity.\n\nIf you want to risk it, use the Quantum Entanglement Device schematic to build it here, in your room in the Lodge.\n\nTo build it, you will need:\n\n10 Quantum Essences\n1 Adaptive Frame\n1 Isocentered Magnet\n1 Tau Grade Rheostat\n\nSafe travels,\nA friend\n\nP.S. - Do NOT put a Grav Drive in it."
msgstr ""

