#. List: 1
#. EDID: SFFL_Anchorpoint_TextSlate_ValLetter
#. REC: BOOK:DESC
msgctxt "00248F"
msgid "Mi muñequita,\n\nI hope you are well and work is not too hard. I am writing with some good news that I know will brighten your day.\n\nGabriel's recital was wonderful! He played perfectly and was given an award for best performance. I tell you, he truly has a talent for music. He reminds me very much of you at his age. I've always believed that if you'd have stuck with it, you could have become a successful musician.\n\nI'll send you a recording of his playing as soon as I can. I think you'll be very proud and impressed.\n\nHow are things at the station? I hope that man Rishi is not working you too hard. I'm grateful for his timely help, but I tell you, Valeria, I don't trust him. Make sure to be firm about your intention to leave just as soon as the debt is paid. Don't let him keep you there indefinitely. My heart tells me that he is a man who will use you for as long as he can get away with it. Don't let him!\n\nWe miss you so much, Valeria. Every day I pray that you will be safe and that you'll come home to us soon. Gabriel is eager to show his mother all the new pieces that he's learned.\n\nWith love,\n\nMom\n\n"
msgstr ""

