msgid "Clue 1:\n\"Before being welcomed by the station, I gazed upon my vessel. With refuse as my neighbor, I scuttled this clue under a melancholic compatriot.\"\n\nClue 2:\n\"Lonely in a crowd, with voices and music fighting for dominance, I gazed up and saw a stoic companion. Broken like me, I trusted the clue's safekeeping to this overseer.\"\n\nClue 3:\n\"Pushed into a corner and ignored like garbage, I remain. Eager to be forgotten, this clue hangs like a fly caught in a web.\"\n\nClue 4:\n\"In the home of the beast and their maker, I consider my circumstance. To elevate my spirits, I must pull myself up from my misery to hide this clue.\"\n\nClue 5:\n\"In the Divine's chambers, I stand a trespasser. I hoped the inner sanctum would bring pride, but all that remains is ridicule. I place the final clue hurriedly, unable to stand this night.\""
