#. List: 1
#. EDID: SFBGS00DDR005_Slate01
#. REC: BOOK:DESC
msgctxt "00250D"
msgid "Readings for life from the station were somewhat correct. It looks like a sprawling hive did exist, but it's dormant. Initial probings into the sacs read lifeless which confirms that.\n\nHowever, life does exist in the body of water. We need to cross-reference the organisms with our database, but I'm convinced we have discovered a new species.\n\nI have sent a request up to the station to bring down supplies and equipment to help establish a base of operations."
msgstr ""

#. List: 1
#. EDID: SFBGS00DDR005_Slate02
#. REC: BOOK:DESC
msgctxt "002511"
msgid "Marigoldelli Planktos (name is still a work in progress) has been an interesting discovery, to say the least. From our experiments, it seems to be a mixotroph. Tends to lean on the photosynthetic processes more since there's really nothing to feed on while they're in isolation.\n\n"
msgstr ""

#. List: 1
#. EDID: SFFL_Anchorpoint_TextSlate_ColstonMessage
#. REC: BOOK:DESC
msgctxt "002517"
msgid "Saint,\n\nI got word about that Fleet crew who hit your place. I'm sure I don't have to tell you that those weren't my guys. It's a tough break, but there's nothing I can do.\n\nRest assured, our agreement stands as long as you keep the credits coming. Speaking of which, you're late on the month's dues. Don't make me send someone to remind you.\n\n- Colston"
