#. List: 1
#. EDID: SFFL_SE_BBI_DataSlate18
#. REC: BOOK:DESC
msgctxt "00255C"
msgid "Ohnrak Ka'dic\n\nBy the breath of the serpent, I greet you.\n\nDuring my vigil, I felt a rhythm stir in the dark. Soft and steady as scales over tiled floor. I shaped it into a verse. I offer it humbly, unsure if it honors the Serpent or strays into apocrypha.\n\n\"Beneath the Scales\"\nBeneath the scales, I sleep in turns,\nCoiled breath where starlight burns.\nO Serpent vast, unwind my mind,\nYour silence calls. I answer, blind.\n\nIf this is unworthy, I will forget it. If not, I humbly offer it as prayer at our next conclave.\n\n-Adherent Tal Varas\n\n\n"
msgstr ""

#. List: 1
#. EDID: SFFL_SE_BBI_DataSlate21
#. REC: BOOK:DESC
msgctxt "00255E"
msgid "Things Still Busted (and whose fault it is):\n\nStarboard inertia stabilizers still drifting. Milo said he would \"eyeball the calibration.\" Idiot.\n\nReactor coolant line #2 leaking again. Probably because Ellis \"fixed it\" with duct wrap and a prayer.\n\nHead 3 doesn't flush. No one admits to it, but I know it was Torres. The guy is massive, eats garbage, and spends too much time in there for it not to be him. Disgusting.\n\nIf this tub makes it to Neon I'm done. Stinking like fish every day at Ebbside is better than this.\n\nEng. Darrin Ko\n\n\n"
msgstr ""

#. List: 1
#. EDID: SFFL_SE_BBI_DataSlate20
#. REC: BOOK:DESC
msgctxt "002560"
msgid "Private Note: Crew Risks, Updated\n\nBex is solid. She still covers me in firefights and doesn't ask where the credits came from. We need her.\n\nAiken is fine. Take him or leave him, but Bex likes him so he gets a pass.\n\nTuro? Sloppy, talks too loud when he's drunk and you can forget getting any work out of him for at least a week after he's been paid. It's hard enough to even find him.\n\nIf this new gig goes sideways, I already know whose fault it will be and who is getting spaced.\n\n\n"
msgstr ""

#. List: 1
#. EDID: SFFL_SE_BBI_DataSlate19
#. REC: BOOK:DESC
msgctxt "002562"
msgid "Journal Entry \nPassenger Deck C, Cassiopeia Transit 1\n\n\nDay 4. I've memorized the sound the drive makes when they spool up for a jump. Low and slow, like a heartbeat too tired to finish.\n\nI tried talking to the woman across the hall in B17 again, but she said five words and closed her door. Again.\n\nI get it. Space changes people. But we've got almost a week left on this boat and I think time would go much faster if we had people to talk to. Oh well.\n\n\n"
msgstr ""

#. List: 1
#. EDID: SFFL_SE_BBI_DataSlate01
#. REC: BOOK:DESC
msgctxt "002564"
msgid "For Tam and the kids, my love and my life.\n\nIf you're reading this, it means someone found me. I'm so grateful.\n\nMy ship broke apart fast. One second I was mining a vein, the next was a bright flash then silence and stars. I must have hit a pressurized pocket of gas. The explosion destroyed the ship before I could blink. I'm still strapped into my favorite chair, floating through the black. So I'm comfortable, at least. It's quiet out here. Peaceful, in a strange way.\n\nI know I won't make it home. The oxygen's almost gone, and there's nothing I can do. I wanted you to know I wasn't afraid. Not really. I'm thinking of you. Your voices. Your faces. You kept me steady, even out here. \n\nTell the kids I was smiling at the end. Because I was.\n\nAll my love,\n\n-Raph\n\n"
msgstr ""

#. List: 1
#. EDID: SFFL_SE_BBI_DataSlate02
#. REC: BOOK:DESC
msgctxt "002566"
msgid "To-do, orbital day 12\n\nRecalibrate Grav Drive spin up sequence. Captain is saying it still takes too long.\n\nRecord message for Dad's birthday. Make sure to send it today or it won't get there in time.\n\nMessage Juno about that hiking trip on Niira and make sure she knows it's only a week away.\n\nActually cook something for dinner tonight. So sick of nutrient paste.\n\nLook into the pressure warning light for the reactor. Still no idea what's going on there, it's probably fine.\n\n"
msgstr ""

#. List: 1
#. EDID: SFFL_SE_BBI_DataSlate03
#. REC: BOOK:DESC
msgctxt "002568"
msgid "Woke up dreaming of Sol again. Sun through the kitchen window, a bird singing outside. Like that still exists. I only ever saw it at the old theater on Akila before they tore it down, but in my dream I'm actually there.\n\nScheduled to dock with the Kapisi this evening. After that, it's just a short jump to Jemison. Been a long haul. Can't wait to see real clouds again. And Arthur, of course.\n\nI'm kinda sick of waiting, to be honest. If he doesn't go for it this time then I might actually propose. We'll see what happens.\n\n"
msgstr ""

#. List: 1
#. EDID: SFFL_SE_BBI_DataSlate04
#. REC: BOOK:DESC
msgctxt "00256A"
msgid "The price of mutiny\n\n"
msgstr ""

