#. List: 1
#. EDID: SFFL_SE_BBI_DataSlate09
#. REC: BOOK:DESC
msgctxt "002574"
msgid "Jagger,\n\nSysDef's hot on our tail. We've been keeping the Grav Drives spun up as much as we can, but Garza thinks we'll blow them out before we hit Kryx. I think Garza is an idiot, so I'm sure the drive will hold.\n\nIf for whatever reason you don't see me, get to my locker before Brock and give my gun to Karo. Don't listen to Brock if he tells you the gun is his. He's lying, I never lost that card game.\n\n-Cyril\n"
msgstr ""

#. List: 1
#. EDID: SFFL_SE_BBI_DataSlate10
#. REC: BOOK:DESC
msgctxt "002576"
msgid "Taka Mitsune, personal slate\nMeeting notes - Dated 08.14.2330\n\n09:00 - meeting delayed as shinji isn't here yet\n09:18 - shinji arrives, meeting begins\n09:30 - marketing plan review (shinji wants to change the plan again! ugh...)\n10:15 - sync with engineering on current delays. something to do with...something. i missed the last bit, will have to follow-up after.\n10:30 - shinji giving the engineers a hard time again\n11:00 - meeting breaks. \n\nAction items:\n\nfollow up with engineering and apologize\n\nbring the bad news to the marketing team\n"
msgstr ""

#. List: 1
#. EDID: SFFL_SE_BBI_DataSlate11
#. REC: BOOK:DESC
msgctxt "002578"
msgid "Property of GalBank, New Atlantis\n"
msgstr ""

#. List: 1
#. EDID: SFFL_SE_BBI_DataSlate12
#. REC: BOOK:DESC
msgctxt "00257A"
msgid "Property of GalBank, New Atlantis\n"
msgstr ""

#. List: 1
#. EDID: SFFL_SE_BBI_DataSlate17
#. REC: BOOK:DESC
msgctxt "00257C"
msgid "Operations Log\nCrewmember: Edgar Tavore\nShip: Transport - Golden Horizon\nRoute: Alpha Centauri, Volii, Cheyenne \n\nMy shift ran smooth:\n\n43 passengers on departure, dropped 18 at Volii and picked up 12 more before final leg to Cheyenne.\n\nMinor customs delay at Volii. A dock security alarm was going off, not our problem.\n\nDocked at Akila just after 1800. Secondary hatch 2 jammed again but we logged it.\n\nHelped offload livestock (again, ugh). No major incidents.\n\nLeft for return leg to Jemison on time.\n\nStill drifting 0.3% on grav stabilizers under load. Logged for maintenance. Stars were quiet. No complaints.\n\n-E. Tavore, Deckhand 2nd Class\n\n\n"
msgstr ""

#. List: 1
#. EDID: SFFL_SE_BBI_DataSlate23
#. REC: BOOK:DESC
msgctxt "00257E"
msgid "Engineering Inventory -- Mid-Cycle Audit\nQuartermaster T. Hsu\n\n2x Class C reactor cores (one cracked, flagged red)\n\n4x fusion stabilizer rods (used, low efficiency; we need new ones asap)\n\n1x auxiliary Grav Drive relay (UC surplus issue, acceptable integrity)\n\n7x emergency bypass fuses (down from 12, someone is not properly logging burns)\n\n\nNote to command: we're running into daily inconsistencies with the inventory reports from 3rd shift. Somebody needs to check on them and find out what the hell they're doing.\n\n\n"
msgstr ""

#. List: 1
#. EDID: SFFL_SE_BBI_DataSlate24
#. REC: BOOK:DESC
msgctxt "002580"
msgid "Unknown Device Observation Log\nCycle 118\n\nThe device pulsed at 03:47 again. No observable phenomena, we just sort of... felt it. Everyone in the chamber reported nausea; some described hearing music \"from behind their own voice,\" if that makes any sense.\n\nRecorder logs show corrupted timecode. Rebooting did nothing. Recommend immediate review by Constellation, or maybe Ryujin R&D. Preferably not both.\n\n\n\n<image name='' caption=''>"
msgstr ""

#. List: 1
#. EDID: SFFL_SE_BBI_DataSlate25
#. REC: BOOK:DESC
msgctxt "002582"
msgid "Experimental Grav Drive Test Report\nEngineering Bay 3B\n\nAdjusted field compression ratio by 0.04% to stabilize observed sublight re-entry spin.\n\nUnexpected result: a secondary micro-jump occurred without jump command (yikes).\n\nOther observations:\n\nTelemetry scrambled\n\nSeveral temperature gauges exceeded specified limits\n\nNav beacon drifted by ~12 minutes standard time during the micro-jump; unclear where that time went\n\nSummary:\n\nIt seems to have worked, but not without significant problems.\n\nOver a dozen Orange-level warnings on first try, 3 Reds, and one Black-level warning from the data recorder. Results are unstable, still analyzing data, but the readings are unlike anything we've observed before.\n\nDO NOT REPLICATE TEST CONDITIONS. Further analysis required.\n\n\n"
msgstr ""

#. List: 1
#. EDID: SFFL_SE_BBI_DataSlate26
#. REC: BOOK:DESC
msgctxt "002584"
msgid "A. Leroux -- LIST Surveyor, Outer Systems Patrol\n\nDidn't sign up for this kind of contact.\n\nWe logged the anomaly from orbit - no emissions, no motion, just sitting there like it had always been part of the rock. Figured it was slag runoff or maybe some dormant biotech trash from the War.\n\nThen it moved.\n\nNot fast, not hostile. Just... aware. Like it noticed me noticing it. And then something changed. The air, the pressure in my head - like being underwater and upside-down all at once. I couldn't feel my boots on the ground. Couldn't remember how long I'd been standing there.\n\nI don't think it touched me. Not physically. But part of it's still in me. Echoes of shapes and colors I don't have names for. Feels wrong when I try to describe it. Feels worse when I don't.\n\nFiling this under high-priority biohazard until someone smarter tells me otherwise.\n\n\n"
msgstr ""

#. List: 1
#. EDID: SFFL_SE_BBI_DataSlate27
#. REC: BOOK:DESC
msgctxt "002586"
msgid "Memo Draft - ENCRYPTION FAILED\nAsset V-11\n\nMade it into the archive sublevel data vault. It was colder than it should've been, strangely. Condensation thick on the walls.\n\nPulled the package, but security AI re-booted early. Had to lock out the entire security root command tree. Meant I couldn't open anymore doors, but neither could their security, so it bought me time.\n\nIf this message gets through: the prototype's real, and it's not a weapon. It's something else.\n\n\n"
msgstr ""

#. List: 1
#. EDID: SFFL_SE_BBI_DataSlate29
#. REC: BOOK:DESC
msgctxt "002588"
msgid "Crew Log: Quartermaster Drel Sorrin\nVessel: UC Bellwether\n\nSomeone's stealing food from the galley again. That's the third time this week, and I'm done playing mystery chef. If you're hungry, ask. If you're lazy, starve.\n\nWe've got enough rations to make it to Cydonia, barely, but if people keep hoarding nutrient packs like we're scrounging the frontier, I'll start locking down sections. Don't think I won't. You want to play feral, I'll feed you like a beast: behind bars.\n\n\n"
msgstr ""

#. List: 1
#. EDID: SFFL_SE_BBI_DataSlate30
#. REC: BOOK:DESC
msgctxt "00258A"
msgid "Personal Log: T. Serano\n\nLocation: Ryujin Research Facility \"Chiron\"\nStatus: Unsent Draft\n\nRyujin promised a bonus. A \"hazard stipend,\" they called it. No details, just a cred number, and a big one. Seemed like a good idea at the time.\n\nWhat they didn't say is that we'd be testing the drug on ourselves. Said it was stable, said the neurological side effects we had heard about were \"understated and controlled.\" But I've watched three coworkers drop into seizures, and one just walked into the reactor chamber like it was nothing. I can still hear his screams.\n\nNo more messages coming in from HQ. Feeds are scrubbed. The slates don't sync with the DB anymore. If you find this, tell someone we weren't volunteers. They made us lab rats.\n\n\n"
msgstr ""

#. List: 1
#. EDID: SFFL_SE_BBI_DataSlate33
#. REC: BOOK:DESC
msgctxt "00258F"
msgid "We ran a ton of contraband planetside, but there were UC Vanguard folks buzzing around.\n\nWe left the Moon Jumper at the coordinates contained - we couldn't get it off planet in time.  If you could, grab it and her goods before circling back.\n\n\n"
msgstr ""

#. List: 1
#. EDID: SFFL_SE_BBI_DataSlate34
#. REC: BOOK:DESC
msgctxt "002591"
msgid "02.21.2141\n\nHouston, Grav Drive test commencing shortly.\n\nAll systems green. Grav Drive powering up.\n\n\nGetting a lot of noise on the reads here.  \n\nMultiple anomalous events - we're seeing cascading electromagnetic field generation and destruction.\n\nStability is holding though, proceeding with jump in 3, 2...\n\n\n"
msgstr ""

#. List: 1
#. EDID: SFFL_SE_BBI_DataSlate35
#. REC: BOOK:DESC
msgctxt "002593"
msgid "EVA scheduled for 0600.\n\nRepair of platinum shielding above Hab and CenCom.\n\nDue to nature of repairs - we will be untethered. Bring ample backup fuel in case of inadvertent station deorbit.\n\n\n"
msgstr ""

